  "title": "Manager/Senior Manager/Deputy General Manager Digital Yield Management",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong></p><h3>1. Manage Internal Digitalisation and Process Improvement Projects (Commercial)</h3><ul><li><p>Lead and manage ongoing digitalization and process improvement initiatives within the commercial function.</p></li><li><p>Engage and align relevant internal stakeholders to ensure project buy-in and smooth execution.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and manage core project team members to improve project speed, quality, and effectiveness.</p></li><li><p>Deliver project outcomes within agreed timelines and scope.</p></li><li><p>Provide regular progress updates to management and refine project plans as required.</p></li></ul><h3>2. Review and Improve Commercial Processes</h3><ul><li><p>Conduct in-depth reviews of existing commercial processes to identify gaps, inefficiencies, and pain points.</p></li><li><p>Develop a strong understanding of the current business model to align improvement initiatives with business needs.</p></li><li><p>Propose detailed and practical solutions for identified pain points, including digital and emerging technology solutions.</p></li><li><p>Report progress and recommendations to management, adjusting project plans where necessary.</p></li></ul><h3>3. Coordinate and Set Up New Projects</h3><ul><li><p>Develop clear and detailed project plans aligned with management’s strategic direction.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with relevant internal and external parties to initiate and execute new projects.</p></li><li><p>Manage project teams to ensure timely and high-quality delivery.</p></li><li><p>Provide ongoing reporting to management and fine-tune project plans as needed.</p></li></ul><h3>4. Management Support</h3><ul><li><p>Provide ad-hoc support to management on project-related and business initiatives as required.</p></li></ul><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Strong logical thinking and open, effective communication skills.</p></li><li><p>Excellent analytical and problem-solving abilities.</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working in a fast-paced, growth-oriented environment.</p></li><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or higher.</p></li><li><p>Proven experience managing international projects and multiple stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Experience in team and people management.</p></li><li><p>Experience living and working in different countries, with a strong understanding of cultural diversity and its impact on business.</p></li></ul>",
